## Bug fixes during CP2

### Bug 1 — Student picker empty
`listStudents({ limit: 500 })` exceeded `listStudentsQuerySchema` max of 200. Zod rejected
the request, Promise.all caught it silently, no state setter ran.
**Fix:** changed to `listStudents({ limit: 200 })`.

### Bug 2 — Monolithic Promise.all silences partial failures
The mount `useEffect` used `Promise.all([...]).then([all 4 setters]).catch(() => {})`.
One rejection (the students 500 call) prevented all four setters from ever running.
**Fix:** split into four independent `.then(setter).catch(...)` chains, matching the
pattern used on the fee catalog page (`fees/page.tsx`).

### Bug 3 — HTTP 304 on fee-items and academic-years returns no body
NestJS/Express adds `ETag` headers to GET responses by default. On subsequent browser
loads the browser sent `If-None-Match`; NestJS returned 304 with no body; `apiFetch`
hit `response.ok === false` (304 is not 2xx), parsed no body, threw `ApiError`;
`.catch(() => {})` swallowed it silently.
**Fix:** added `cache: "no-store"` to the `fetch()` call in `apps/web/src/lib/api-client.ts`
(before `...rest` so callers can still override). Applies globally to all `apiFetch` calls.

### Bug 4 — Fee categories empty despite 200 response
`listFeeCategories()` defaults to `active: true`. If an admin had deactivated a fee
category, it disappeared from the discounts modal even though active fee items still
existed under it (fee items have an independent `active` flag). The API returned `[]`
with a valid 200, so no error surfaced.
**Fix:** discounts page calls `listFeeCategories({ includeInactive: true })` and
`listFeeItems({ includeInactive: true })`. Discount rules legitimately target deactivated
fee items/categories — a scholarship applied to a retired tuition line must still be
visible and manageable.
Changed silent `.catch(() => {})` to `.catch(e => console.error('[DiscountsPage]', e))`
on fee-catalog and academic-years calls so future API errors surface in DevTools.

